what_failed: Regression (0.67x): Created CTEs to pre-filter dimension tables (item and date_dim), then computed item-specific average discounts in a single pass using those filtered dimensions, and finally joined everything together with the main condition. This eliminates the correlated subquery and reduces redundant scans.
why_it_failed: Split a simple OR condition (t_hour BETWEEN 10 AND 11 OR t_hour BETWEEN 16 AND 17) into UNION ALL of two separate web_sales scans. This doubles the fact table scan. DuckDB handles same-column OR ranges efficiently in a single scan — the UNION ALL adds materialization overhead with zero selectivity benefit.
